comments.body:
Without the fix the test I created raises the expected assertion:
{{
tests/TestClient.cc:574: Assertion: assertion failed [Expression: calculate_interval(&started, &completion_timestamp) < 2]
Failures !!!
Run: 46   Failure total: 1   Failures: 1   Errors: 0
}}

With the fix, the tests complete successfully.
{{
OK (46)
}}

One super nit [~michim]:

{noformat}
+        int tmp = (int) (long) data;
+        CPPUNIT_ASSERT_EQUAL(tmp, rc);
{noformat}

calling tmp expected_rc or such makes it a tiny bit more readable. 

But more importantly and related to one method this patch modifies, do you know why there's no calls to enter/leave_critical in send_info_packet? It modifies &zh->to_send, and everything else in that file that does so holds a lock to do it.
